Food tasted fine, though nothing exceptional; service was poor. Went for an early dinner at 5:00 P.M. on a Saturday and was not given the dim sum menu. Upon asking for it, was told that only a limited selection of the dishes were available, and then that they were out of several regular menu items. Eventually ordered the maca chicken soup (would recommend), blanched seasonal vegetables (oily), nori shumai (sloppily put together), steamed short ribs (extremely fatty), beef omasum (decent), beef meatballs (strangely bouncy), and beef ho fun (far too greasy). When paying the check, they gave us attitude about the tip!

This is a hidden gem of a "cha chan tang" restaurant as it is further south on Wentworth then Chinatown proper. Not only do they serve dim sum and your typical "cha chan tang" / Hong Kong cafe style fare they also bake their own buns and  pastries on site. Their dinner menu also stands out as they have several claypot dishes that are fantastic and a board featuring nightly specials, it's written in Chinese but do inquire about them when you dine.  Free parking and almost always a table available are also things to consider.

When I'm in the mood for some hot milk tea, I usually find myself at St. Alp's, but when I don't feel like spending $5 a pop, Dim Dim offers a good alternative for about $1-2 when I'm in the area.  Surprisingly, they have a decent selection of baked goods. My friend and I tried their Asian version of a fish filet sandwich with lettuce, tomato and mayo. It was pretty good. I would definitely get it again. I also purchased a few a la carte dim sum items, which were decent.  In addition to selling drinks and baked goods, this place also is a restaurant which offers Chinese dishes and dim sum. There's also a parking lot, but spaces are limited.

I love this place!! I dare to say they have the best Dim Sum in Chinatown with reasonable price. I had my rehearsal dinner there last summer with 40 guests. Yup, it was after business hour and we took up their whole place. We ordered tons of dim sum, small chinese dishes and smoothies, and the bill was less than $500. HOW AMAZING! I strongly recommend this dim sum place to everyone.
